{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbd92c2e4-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s9308"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9308"},"text":"§ 9308.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Civil penalty","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A surety corporation is liable to the United States Government for a civil penalty of at least $500 but not more than $5,000 for violating section 9304, 9305, or 9306 of this title. A civil action under this section may be brought in a judicial district in which a civil action may be brought against the corporation under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s9307"},"text":"section 9307 of this title","children":[],"tail":". A penalty imposed under this section does not affect the validity of a contract made by the surety corporation."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbd92c2e5-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1049"},"text":"96 Stat. 1049","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbd92c2e6-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idbd92c2e7-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idbd92c2e8-47c4-11f1-bea6-82cea744851c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],